value.value: Adult intrinsic neuron with ipsilateral arbors in a single VNC neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It is a primary neuron of the 16B hemilineage (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). It receives input in the T3 leg neuropil and sends output to the T3 leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the metathoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).

It receives input in the T1 leg neuropil and sends output to the T1 leg neuropil (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is glutamate (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 6 of these cells per organism and their somas are found in the prothoracic neuromere (Takemura et al., 2023; Marin et al., 2024).
